141
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,666
[CARLA] What in the world could
we possibly be preparing for?!

142
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,416
I think this might
help you overcome the trauma

143
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,041
you've experienced, Carla.

144
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:55,291
[WENDY] I dunno how this'll
help but it is kinda fun!

145
00:07:55,375 --> 00:07:56,708
[CANA] I'm a little
disturbed that you guys

146
00:07:56,791 --> 00:07:58,416
are so into this...

147
00:07:58,500 --> 00:07:59,958
Listen up!
If we're going to make

148
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:02,916
a second attempt at the
first picnic of our lives...

149
